assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Sanyei Corporation engages in the wholesale and retail of furniture and houseware, fashion accessories, and home appliances in Japan and internationally. The company offers furniture, such as beds and tables, as well as housewares comprising pots and tableware under the MINT and Villeroy & Bochb brands; fashion accessories, such as trolley luggage products, pouches, bags, and shoes under the BIRKENSTOCK and Kipling brand names; and beauty and kitchen appliances the Vitantonio, mod's hair, and MULTI CHEF brands. It also provides pets, pet products, transport materials, and industrial goods under the Pepica brand; iron pots under the CHASSEUR brand; cast-aluminum cookware under the WOLL brand name; watches under the KERBHOLZ brand; and home appliances under the ION-Sei brand name. In addition, the company operates a boutique under the Quorinest name, which offers various apparel and accessories; and pet salons and animal clinics. Further, the company provides logistic services, including product planning, development, and delivery services; and after sales services, as well as manufactures home appliances. The company was formerly known as SANYEI Boeki and changed its name to Sanyei Corporation in 1971. Sanyei Corporation was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
